searchData={"items":[{"type":"behaviour","title":"erltity","doc":"","ref":"erltity.html"},{"type":"callback","title":"erltity.create/1","doc":"","ref":"erltity.html#c:create/1"},{"type":"function","title":"erltity.create/2","doc":"Saves a new entity of type EntityName with the given CreateRequest.","ref":"erltity.html#create/2"},{"type":"type","title":"erltity.cursor/0","doc":"","ref":"erltity.html#t:cursor/0"},{"type":"type","title":"erltity.db_driver/0","doc":"","ref":"erltity.html#t:db_driver/0"},{"type":"callback","title":"erltity.delete/1","doc":"","ref":"erltity.html#c:delete/1"},{"type":"function","title":"erltity.delete/2","doc":"Deletes an existing entity of type EntityName with the given Id.","ref":"erltity.html#delete/2"},{"type":"callback","title":"erltity.find/1","doc":"","ref":"erltity.html#c:find/1"},{"type":"callback","title":"erltity.find/2","doc":"","ref":"erltity.html#c:find/2"},{"type":"function","title":"erltity.find/2","doc":"Finds an entity of type EntityName with the given Id.","ref":"erltity.html#find/2"},{"type":"function","title":"erltity.find/3","doc":"Finds entities of type EntityName that match the given Filters and Opts, Opts can include pagination options like page, page_size, and offset.","ref":"erltity.html#find/3"},{"type":"type","title":"erltity.find_opts/0","doc":"","ref":"erltity.html#t:find_opts/0"},{"type":"type","title":"erltity.opts/0","doc":"","ref":"erltity.html#t:opts/0"},{"type":"type","title":"erltity.path/0","doc":"","ref":"erltity.html#t:path/0"},{"type":"function","title":"erltity.register/2","doc":"Registers a schema from the given path and generates the new Erlang module.","ref":"erltity.html#register/2"},{"type":"type","title":"erltity.register_opts/0","doc":"","ref":"erltity.html#t:register_opts/0"},{"type":"type","title":"erltity.schemas_path/0","doc":"","ref":"erltity.html#t:schemas_path/0"},{"type":"function","title":"erltity.start_link/2","doc":"Starts the erltity application connecting to the database using the given driver and options.","ref":"erltity.html#start_link/2"},{"type":"function","title":"erltity.stop/1","doc":"Stops the erltity application.","ref":"erltity.html#stop/1"},{"type":"callback","title":"erltity.update/2","doc":"","ref":"erltity.html#c:update/2"},{"type":"function","title":"erltity.update/3","doc":"Updates an existing entity of type EntityName with the given Id and UpdateRequest.","ref":"erltity.html#update/3"},{"type":"module","title":"erltity_generator","doc":"","ref":"erltity_generator.html"},{"type":"function","title":"erltity_generator.generate/2","doc":"","ref":"erltity_generator.html#generate/2"},{"type":"module","title":"erltity_parser","doc":"","ref":"erltity_parser.html"},{"type":"function","title":"erltity_parser.parse/1","doc":"","ref":"erltity_parser.html#parse/1"},{"type":"module","title":"erltity_sup","doc":"","ref":"erltity_sup.html"},{"type":"function","title":"erltity_sup.init/1","doc":"","ref":"erltity_sup.html#init/1"},{"type":"function","title":"erltity_sup.start_link/2","doc":"","ref":"erltity_sup.html#start_link/2"},{"type":"extras","title":"Overview","doc":"# Erltity\n![erltity status](https://github.com/yagogarea/erltity/actions/workflows/ci.yml/badge.svg)\n![Docs Status](https://github.com/yagogarea/erltity/workflows/Docs/badge.svg)\n\nErltity is an Erlang library that simplifies database interaction by generating Erlang code from entity definitions. It provides a set of functions to easily communicate with your database.\n\nErltity parses your entity definitions and generates Erlang code that allows you to interact with your database.","ref":"readme.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Setup - Overview","doc":"Add `erltity`, the database driver and the parser that you want to use as dependencies in your `rebar.config` file. For example, to use PostgreSQL with the `epgsql` driver, using the JSON Schema parser, your `rebar.config` should look like this:\n\n```erlang\n{deps, [\n  {erltity, {git_subdir, \"https://github.com/yagogarea/erltity.git\", {branch, \"main\"}, \"apps/erltity\"}},\n  {erltity_epgsql, {git_subdir, \"https://github.com/yagogarea/erltity.git\", {branch, \"main\"}, \"apps/erltity_epgsql\"}},\n  {erltity_json_schema_parser, {git_subdir, \"https://github.com/yagogarea/erltity.git\", {branch, \"main\"}, \"apps/erltity_json_schema_parser\"}}\n]}.\n```","ref":"readme.html#setup"},{"type":"extras","title":"Supported Features - Overview","doc":"Currently, `erltity` supports:\n- **Databases**:\n      \n  - [PostgreSQL](https://www.postgresql.org/)\n\n- **Entity definition formats**:\n\n  - [JSON Schema Draft-07](http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#)","ref":"readme.html#supported-features"},{"type":"extras","title":"Usage - Overview","doc":"```erlang\n1> erltity:start_link(epgsql, Opts). % Provide your database connection options\n\n2> erltity:register(<<\"test/schemas/dog.json\">>, #{}).\n\n3> dog:create(#{<<\"name\">> => <<\"Nala\">>, <<\"breed\">> => <<\"Chihuahua\">>}).\n{ok,#{<<\"breed\">> => <<\"Chihuahua\">>,<<\"id\">> => 1,\n      <<\"name\">> => <<\"Nala\">>}}\n\n4> dog:find(1).\n{ok,#{<<\"breed\">> => <<\"Chihuahua\">>,<<\"id\">> => 1,\n      <<\"name\">> => <<\"Nala\">>}}\n```\nFor practical examples, check out the examples directory.","ref":"readme.html#usage"},{"type":"extras","title":"Register Function and Module Generation - Overview","doc":"The `register` function generates a module named after the entity definition with functions to interact with the database. This module is loaded into the system for immediate use.\n\nOptionally, the module can be saved to disk with the `#{save_module => Path}` option.\n\nWhen using a SQL database, if the target table does not exist at command execution, Erltity attempts to create it by inferring the table structure from the entity definition types.\n\nSaving the generated table creation command to a file is possible with the `#{save_create_table => Path}` option.\n\nThe generated module includes the following functions for interacting with the database:\n\n| Function   | Description                                          |\n|------------|------------------------------------------------------|\n| `create/1` | Inserts a new record into the database               |\n| `update/2` | Updates an existing record identified by its ID     |\n| `delete/1` | Deletes a record identified by its ID                |\n| `find/1`   | Retrieves a single record by its ID                   |\n| `find/2`   | Retrieves records filtered according to specified fields |","ref":"readme.html#register-function-and-module-generation"},{"type":"extras","title":"License - Overview","doc":"This project is licensed under the MIT License - see the [LICENSE](LICENSE) file for details.","ref":"readme.html#license"},{"type":"extras","title":"Contributing - Overview","doc":"Contributions are welcome! If you find a bug or have a feature request, feel free to open an issue or submit a pull request. See our [contributing guide](CONTRIBUTING.md) for more details.","ref":"readme.html#contributing"},{"type":"extras","title":"Contributing","doc":"# Contributing to Erltity","ref":"contributing.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Reporting Bugs - Contributing","doc":"If you find a bug in Erltity, please open an issue on the [GitHub Issues page](https://github.com/yagogarea/erltity/issues)\nand provide as much detail as possible. Include the following information:\n- A clear description of the bug\n- Steps to reproduce the bug\n- Expected behavior vs actual behavior\n- Any relevant logs or error messages\n\nI will do my best to address the issue as soon as possible, if you want to help, you can also submit a pull request with a fix.","ref":"contributing.html#reporting-bugs"},{"type":"extras","title":"Feature Requests - Contributing","doc":"If you have a feature request, please open an issue and describe the feature in detail. I will review the request and wive you feedback as soon as possible. If you want to implement the feature yourself, feel free to submit a pull request.","ref":"contributing.html#feature-requests"},{"type":"extras","title":"Submitting Pull Requests - Contributing","doc":"If you want to contribute code to `erltity` make sure you create a new branch for your pull request, give it a descriptive name using the\n[Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/) format for the branch name (e.g., `feat/add-new-feature`, `fix/fix-bug`, etc.) and be sure to include a clear description of the changes you made in the pull request description.","ref":"contributing.html#submitting-pull-requests"},{"type":"extras","title":"After opening issue or pull request - Contributing","doc":"I will review your issue or pull request as soon as possible. Please be patient, as I may not be able to respond immediately. If you have any questions or need clarification, feel free to ask in the issue or pull request comments.","ref":"contributing.html#after-opening-issue-or-pull-request"},{"type":"extras","title":"License","doc":"MIT License\n\nCopyright (c) 2025 Santiago Garea Cidre\n\nPermission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person obtaining a copy\nof this software and associated documentation files (the \"Software\"), to deal\nin the Software without restriction, including without limitation the rights\nto use, copy, modify, merge, publish, distribute, sublicense, and/or sell\ncopies of the Software, and to permit persons to whom the Software is\nfurnished to do so, subject to the following conditions:\n\nThe above copyright notice and this permission notice shall be included in all\ncopies or substantial portions of the Software.\n\nTHE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED \"AS IS\", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR\nIMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY,\nFITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE AND NONINFRINGEMENT. IN NO EVENT SHALL THE\nAUTHORS OR COPYRIGHT HOLDERS BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES OR OTHER\nLIABILITY, WHETHER IN AN ACTION OF CONTRACT, TORT OR OTHERWISE, ARISING FROM,\nOUT OF OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE SOFTWARE OR THE USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN THE\nSOFTWARE.","ref":"license.html"}],"proglang":"erlang","content_type":"text/markdown","producer":{"name":"ex_doc","version":"0.38.2"}}